summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2015 CHRYSLER 200. THE CONTACT STATED THAT THE VEHICLE HESITATED WHILE BEING OPERATED AT LOW SPEEDS. THE CONTACT ALSO STATED THAT THE GEAR SHIFTER DID NOT OPERATE AS INTENDED. THE VEHICLE WAS TAKEN TO ATLANTA WEST WHERE THE DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS WERE NOT DISCLOSED. THE BATTERY WAS REPLACED, BUT THE CHECK ENGINE WARNING INDICATOR ILLUMINATED AND THE VEHICLE STILL EXPERIENCED HESITATION. THE MANUFACTURER WAS NOTIFIED OF THE FAILURE AND OFFERED NO ASSISTANCE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS APPROXIMATELY 37,029.
